@startmindmap
* Prototype Capability Lenses (USF)
** Lens 1 - Concept Coverage [high]
*** mod + modpack composition
*** metric + metric_set declarations
*** scale contracts
*** phenomenon_realizer declarations
*** phenomenon + phenomenon_model declarations
*** capability-channel usage contracts
** Lens 2 - Scale Ladder [high]
*** coarse-to-mid scaffolding must be valid
*** human-band depth must be rich near 10^0 m regime
*** parent closure must remain legal for active windows
** Lens 3 - Lifecycle [high]
*** startup = deterministic bootstrap + seal
*** runtime = ordered substrate->realizer->phenomenon->commit phases
*** rebuild = derived state drop/rebuild without canonical loss
** Lens 4 - Capability Surface [high]
*** mesh/material/collider path required
*** at least one non-mesh channel required
*** evaluator hook path exercised in at least one channel
** Lens 5 - Recognition Direction [medium]
*** detailed runtime state should remain mappable to higher-level semantic concepts
*** this is directionally required, not full-fidelity simulation mandate
@endmindmap

@startuml
title Prototype Acceptance Gate
start
:verify script-first authority contracts;
:verify minimal valid scale ladder and traversal legality;
:verify deterministic behavior for same seed+content+timeline laws;
:verify derived-state rebuild from canonical runtime records;
:verify capability channels are reusable platform surface;
if (all checks pass?) then (yes)
  :prototype acceptance achieved;
else (no)
  :record gaps in intention records and iterate;
endif
stop
@enduml
